---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'BUPA Global Review', href: '/providers/bupa-global' },
  { title: 'SafetyWing Review', href: '/providers/safetywing' },
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Digital Nomads', href: '/insurance-for/digital-nomads' },
  { title: 'Thailand Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Type', bupa: 'Health Insurance', safetywing: 'Travel Medical' },
  { feature: 'Maximum Coverage', bupa: '$2M-Unlimited', safetywing: '$250,000' },
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', bupa: true, safetywing: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', bupa: true, safetywing: 'Limited' },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', bupa: 'Excellent', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Maternity', bupa: 'Optional', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Pre-Existing Conditions', bupa: 'After waiting period', safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Routine Checkups', bupa: true, safetywing: false },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', bupa: true, safetywing: '$100,000' },
  { feature: 'Home Country Coverage', bupa: 'Optional', safetywing: '15 days/90 days' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'bupa', header: 'BUPA Global' },
  { key: 'safetywing', header: 'SafetyWing Nomad' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', bupa: '$200-280/mo', safetywing: '$45/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', bupa: '$350-450/mo', safetywing: '$73/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', bupa: '$400-560/mo', safetywing: '$90/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', bupa: '$700-1,000/mo', safetywing: '$140/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="BUPA Global vs SafetyWing"
  description="Compare BUPA Global and SafetyWing side by side. Premium health insurance vs budget nomad coverage—which is right for you?"
  headline="BUPA Global vs SafetyWing: Premium vs Budget Comparison"
  subheadline="Comprehensive health insurance vs affordable travel medical. Understanding what you're actually comparing."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/compare/bupa-vs-safetywing-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Your Options"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    BUPA Global and SafetyWing serve very different needs. BUPA Global is premium international health insurance with comprehensive coverage. SafetyWing Nomad Insurance is affordable travel medical insurance designed for digital nomads. Comparing them requires understanding that difference.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-yellow-900 mb-2">Important: Different Products</h3>
    <p class="text-yellow-800">
      BUPA Global is <strong>health insurance</strong>—it covers routine care, pre-existing conditions (after waiting periods), and chronic disease management. SafetyWing is <strong>travel medical insurance</strong>—it covers emergencies and unexpected illness but not ongoing health needs.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">BUPA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Comprehensive health insurance</li>
        <li>Excellent mental health coverage</li>
        <li>Pre-existing conditions covered</li>
        <li>Routine care and checkups included</li>
        <li>Premium pricing ($200-400+/mo)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">SafetyWing Nomad</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Travel medical insurance</li>
        <li>Emergency and accident coverage</li>
        <li>No pre-existing condition coverage</li>
        <li>No routine care</li>
        <li>Budget pricing ($45-75/mo)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Need Help Choosing?"
    description="Compare options based on your actual health needs and budget."
    buttonText="See All Options"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    The coverage gap between these two options is significant. BUPA Global covers nearly everything; SafetyWing covers emergencies only.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>What this means in practice:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Break your leg abroad:</strong> Both cover it</li>
    <li><strong>Need therapy for anxiety:</strong> BUPA covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Managing diabetes:</strong> BUPA covers it (after waiting period); SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Annual physical:</strong> BUPA covers it; SafetyWing doesn't</li>
    <li><strong>Having a baby:</strong> BUPA offers maternity add-on; SafetyWing covers complications only</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    The price difference is dramatic—SafetyWing costs roughly 75-80% less than BUPA Global. But you're getting fundamentally different products.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Understanding the price gap:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>BUPA's higher price reflects comprehensive coverage and unlimited benefits</li>
    <li>SafetyWing's low price reflects limited, emergency-only coverage</li>
    <li>The $150-200/month difference pays for routine care, mental health, and chronic condition management</li>
    <li>If you're healthy and just need emergency coverage, SafetyWing's price is appealing</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Consider Your Health Needs"
    description="The right choice depends on what coverage you actually need."
    buttonText="Compare Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> has established relationships with hospitals worldwide and offers direct billing at major facilities. You can often see a doctor without paying upfront.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> works on a reimbursement model. You pay for care and submit claims afterward. They don't have a traditional provider network.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global has a mature claims system with an online portal and app. SafetyWing's claims process is simpler (fewer things to claim) but also less sophisticated.
  </p>

  <h3>Customer Support</h3>
  <p>
    BUPA Global offers 24/7 multilingual support and dedicated case managers for complex situations. SafetyWing has more limited support appropriate for a travel insurance product.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose BUPA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You have ongoing health needs</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage is important</li>
        <li>You want routine checkups covered</li>
        <li>You have or expect pre-existing conditions</li>
        <li>You want comprehensive, worry-free coverage</li>
        <li>You can afford premium pricing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose SafetyWing If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're young and healthy</li>
        <li>You only need emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Budget is your primary concern</li>
        <li>You're a digital nomad moving frequently</li>
        <li>You're comfortable with limited coverage</li>
        <li>You can pay out-of-pocket for routine care</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    This isn't really an apples-to-apples comparison. BUPA Global and SafetyWing serve different purposes at different price points.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>BUPA Global</strong> is the right choice if you want actual health insurance that covers everything from checkups to chronic conditions. It's expensive, but you're getting comprehensive coverage with one of the most respected names in international health insurance.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> is appropriate if you're healthy, budget-conscious, and primarily worried about catastrophic events like accidents or sudden illness. It's not a replacement for health insurance—it's travel medical coverage for people willing to handle routine health expenses out of pocket.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you're unsure, consider: Would you be comfortable paying $200+ out of pocket for a doctor visit or $100+ for prescriptions? If yes, SafetyWing might work. If that sounds stressful, you probably need actual health insurance like BUPA Global.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Find the Right Coverage Level"
    description="See options across the price spectrum based on your needs."
    buttonText="Compare All Options"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
